    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<CommandCallable>, java.util.Collection<CommandCallable>, java.util.List<CommandCallable>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class CommandList
extends java.util.ArrayList<CommandCallable>
    This class is a subclass of ArrayList. This barely differs from a normal ArrayList and just provides some methods for easier sorting commands.

      • getSortedByCategories

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<CommandCallable>> getSortedByCategories()
        Sorts all CommandCallables of this list using their category. All commands with the same category are stored in the same list. Every list gets stored inside a Map. The name of the category is thereby the key.
        Returns:
        a Map containing all commands sorted by their category
